        },
        "rich_text_AJHQPB": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Why Trilogy Rings Feel Balanced and Elegant",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Why Trilogy Rings Feel Balanced and Elegant</h2>",
            "custom_id": "why-trilogy",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_bhGzpc": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Rich Text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Aside from symbolism, trilogy rings are visually appealing because of their balanced design.</p><p>The center diamond usually appears slightly larger, while the two side stones frame it naturally. This arrangement draws attention to the middle stone without making the ring feel overly dramatic.</p><p>For example, the <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/products/trio-flourish-ring\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Trio Flourish Ring \">Trio Flourish Ring </a>uses this balanced structure to create a graceful design where all three diamonds complement each other.</p><p>This harmony is one reason trilogy rings remain a popular alternative to traditional solitaire rings.</p>",
            "custom_id": "clarity",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "image_with_text_XgNzg9": {
          "type": "image_with_text",
          "name": "Image with text ",
