        "rich_text_qwTzXx": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>Make sure to check a diamond’s certificate before you make a purchase, as a diamond with fewer imperfections will come at a higher asking price. Imperfections also give each diamond its own unique character, and to many, these add to its beauty.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_9LDfB8": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "name": "Different Diamond Shapes Can Create Unique Trilogy Styles",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<h2>Different Diamond Shapes Can Create Unique Trilogy Styles</h2><p>Another interesting aspect of <a href=\"https://www.lucirajewelry.com/collections/trilogy-rings\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"trilogy rings\">trilogy rings</a> is the variety of shapes that can be combined.</p><p>Some rings feature three identical diamonds, while others mix shapes to create contrast.</p><p>For instance:</p>",
            "custom_id": "different",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
        "rich_text_XfaQeJ": {
          "type": "rich_text",
          "settings": {
            "content": "<p>1.] The Pear Diamond Three-Stone Ring combines pear shapes for a soft, elegant look.<br/><br/>2.] The Hexa Baguette Trilogy Ring uses baguette stones that add a modern geometric touch.<br/><br/>3.] The Modern Trio Pear Diamond Ring blends contemporary styling with the classic three-stone concept.<br/><br/>By mixing shapes and sizes, designers can create rings that feel both classic and distinctive.</p>",
            "custom_id": "",
            "text_alignment": "left"
          }
        },
